WEBVTT

1
00:00:29.274 --> 00:00:30.942
Emerson. are you with the patient?

2
00:00:32.569 --> 00:00:34.570
Stationed outside her room. ma'am.

3
00:00:34.571 --> 00:00:37.449
Good. I need you to deliver
a message to her nurse.

4
00:00:41.786 --> 00:00:42.954
What are you doing here?

5
00:00:43.580 --> 00:00:45.623
Figured you might need some company.

6
00:00:48.710 --> 00:00:52.796
What I really need is for you
to start the Judicial process

7
00:00:52.797 --> 00:00:54.423
for installing an interim mayor.

8
00:00:54.424 --> 00:00:55.716
Her condition's that bad?

9
00:00:55.717 --> 00:00:58.927
Unlikely to survive the night.
I'll see you at home.

10
00:00:58.928 --> 00:01:00.929
It wants what it wanted three months ago.

11
00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:04.476
but the gas in the mines
didn't quite do the job. right?

12
00:01:05.477 --> 00:01:07.686
The gas in the mines was for Lukas Kyle.

13
00:01:07.687 --> 00:01:09.271
He was in the mines?

14
00:01:09.272 --> 00:01:10.482
He got away.

15
00:01:11.566 --> 00:01:13.401
But the gas did get the mayor.

16
00:01:17.155 --> 00:01:20.492
Well. it sounds like the voice in there
thinks that was a good thing.

17
00:01:22.035 --> 00:01:23.536
Heroic death and all.

18
00:01:25.246 --> 00:01:26.498
And this.

19
00:01:27.791 --> 00:01:30.627
this could stop the need
to put the drugs in the water.

20
00:01:34.380 --> 00:01:35.757
I'll do it for you.

21
00:01:38.593 --> 00:01:40.094
It has to be me.

22
00:01:40.095 --> 00:01:42.514
[Sims] Yeah. I understand.

23
00:01:43.807 --> 00:01:45.683
But you don't have to be alone.

24
00:01:51.397 --> 00:01:53.357
[Amy] When will Mrs. Sims get here?

25
00:01:53.358 --> 00:01:54.734
[Emerson] She's on her way now.

26
00:01:56.528 --> 00:01:58.530
She wants her unconscious
when she arrives.

27
00:02:03.785 --> 00:02:04.994
Hold her down.

28
00:02:10.875 --> 00:02:13.085
- [shushes]
- [groans] What's going on?

29
00:02:13.086 --> 00:02:15.712
- [softly] Okay. Okay. [shushing]
- [sighs] No.

30
00:02:15.713 --> 00:02:18.674
- Hey. Hey. hey. hey.
- [groaning]

31
00:02:18.675 --> 00:02:20.759
- It's okay. It's all right.
- Help! Help!

32
00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:24.180
- Keep her quiet. [shushing]
- [groaning] Help! Help!

33
00:02:26.516 --> 00:02:27.891
[shushes]

34
00:02:27.892 --> 00:02:29.144
[muffled shouting]

35
00:02:32.856 --> 00:02:34.524
[screams]

36
00:02:39.404 --> 00:02:40.864
[screams]

37
00:02:41.656 --> 00:02:43.241
- [Amy grunts] No. no. no. no.
- [shouts]

38
00:02:44.409 --> 00:02:46.535
[grunts. groans]

39
00:02:46.536 --> 00:02:48.163
[Emerson grunting]

40
00:02:55.295 --> 00:02:57.589
- [groans. yells]
- [grunts. pants]

41
00:03:06.181 --> 00:03:09.184
[panting]

42
00:03:12.228 --> 00:03:15.689
[breathes heavily] We have to go. Now.

43
00:03:15.690 --> 00:03:17.609
[pants]

44
00:05:14.017 --> 00:05:16.977
- Hey. Hey. hey. What are you doing?
- We have to call someone.

45
00:05:16.978 --> 00:05:18.438
We have to call someone?

46
00:05:19.063 --> 00:05:20.147
[Daniel] What the fuck?

47
00:05:20.148 --> 00:05:22.357
- They just made a man disappear. okay?
- Goddamn it!

48
00:05:22.358 --> 00:05:24.568
And they're probably listening
through our phones.

49
00:05:24.569 --> 00:05:26.780
- What if Charlotte tries to call?
- You can't...

50
00:05:27.280 --> 00:05:29.990
Daniel. you can't talk to Charlotte.
They'll be monitoring her calls.

51
00:05:29.991 --> 00:05:31.825
We have to get away from here.
I just don't know...

52
00:05:31.826 --> 00:05:33.744
- Wait. What...
- ...if my car is bugged or has a tracker.

53
00:05:33.745 --> 00:05:35.288
What do you think this is?

54
00:05:36.456 --> 00:05:38.165
[pants]

55
00:05:38.166 --> 00:05:41.419
Someone made that man disappear.

56
00:05:43.379 --> 00:05:44.380
Okay?

57
00:05:45.465 --> 00:05:47.467
So now we have to get somewhere safe.

58
00:05:50.887 --> 00:05:52.513
I think I know somewhere.

59
00:05:52.514 --> 00:05:53.515
Where?

60
00:05:56.518 --> 00:05:59.979
Okay. just-just-just...
don't show up until 10:00.

61
00:06:01.106 --> 00:06:02.690
What am I supposed to do until then?

62
00:06:03.483 --> 00:06:05.360
Whatever you do. don't go home.

63
00:06:08.738 --> 00:06:10.114
[coughing]

64
00:06:10.115 --> 00:06:11.533
You'll be all right. Nurse!

65
00:06:17.288 --> 00:06:19.123
- Tell me she's okay. [sobs]
- [Knox] I don't know.

66
00:06:19.124 --> 00:06:20.749
I tried to stay with her.
They wouldn't let me.

67
00:06:20.750 --> 00:06:22.835
- I'm a total piece of shit.
- What are you talking about?

68
00:06:22.836 --> 00:06:24.586
Jules reached out to me for help.

69
00:06:24.587 --> 00:06:27.297
First I ignored her
and then I yelled at her.

70
00:06:27.298 --> 00:06:30.134
You can't beat yourself up.
I left her alone in the mines.

71
00:06:30.135 --> 00:06:32.428
- What happened to her?
- She went in to try and save people.

72
00:06:32.429 --> 00:06:33.846
Of course she did.

73
00:06:33.847 --> 00:06:35.515
They're not gonna let you
see her. [grunts]

74
00:06:51.739 --> 00:06:53.532
[Camille] Hey. Emerson.

75
00:06:53.533 --> 00:06:54.951
She's got a pulse.

76
00:06:56.161 --> 00:06:57.162
Fuck.

77
00:06:58.204 --> 00:07:00.206
[coughing]

78
00:07:02.459 --> 00:07:06.754
Okay. Here. Take this. Breathe. Breathe.
Breathe. Okay. Good.

79
00:07:06.755 --> 00:07:09.006
[breathing deeply]

80
00:07:09.007 --> 00:07:11.717
[raiders speaking indistinctly]

81
00:07:11.718 --> 00:07:13.052
We gotta go. We gotta go.

82
00:07:14.554 --> 00:07:15.638
[coughing]

83
00:07:19.809 --> 00:07:20.935
[Molly] Sheriff.

84
00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:36.283
So. what do you wanna know?

85
00:07:36.284 --> 00:07:38.619
Just wanna confirm cause of death
was rat poison.

86
00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:41.163
- [morgue tech] Can't do that.
- You need more time?

87
00:07:41.164 --> 00:07:42.749
No. I mean. she wasn't poisoned.

88
00:07:43.875 --> 00:07:47.836
I got a full house tonight whose C.O.D.
was aerosol-based rat poison.

89
00:07:47.837 --> 00:07:49.505
Their lungs are fried.

90
00:07:49.506 --> 00:07:51.673
Hers are kitchen clean.

91
00:07:51.674 --> 00:07:53.008
Then what happened?

92
00:07:53.009 --> 00:07:55.303
She was struck
in the back of the head. hard.

93
00:07:55.887 --> 00:07:58.639
Pretty sure by a length of rebar.

94
00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:00.724
There's a ribbed pattern in the wound.

95
00:08:00.725 --> 00:08:03.853
- When?
- By the pooling? [sighs] Couple days.

96
00:08:07.774 --> 00:08:09.108
Where did you find her?

97
00:08:09.109 --> 00:08:12.694
One of the search teams went down
a closed-off tunnel. just to be sure.

98
00:08:12.695 --> 00:08:14.613
Found her way back.

99
00:08:14.614 --> 00:08:18.660
Maybe she was there for some reason.
and a-a ceiling caved in?

100
00:08:19.410 --> 00:08:21.787
- They use rebar...
- No. When I said her lungs were clean.

101
00:08:21.788 --> 00:08:23.581
I meant she didn't die in the mines.

102
00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:27.292
Anyone who dies in there.
and I've seen a bunch over the years.

103
00:08:27.293 --> 00:08:29.504
there's always dust in the lungs.

104
00:08:32.507 --> 00:08:34.508
She was never supposed to be found.

105
00:08:39.681 --> 00:08:41.641
Show me the wound. please.

106
00:08:42.851 --> 00:08:44.519
Billings to Deputy Murphy.

107
00:08:45.395 --> 00:08:46.438
[Murphy] <i>Go ahead. Sheriff.</i>

108
00:08:47.147 --> 00:08:49.691
[Paul] If you see Carla McLain.
tell her to meet me in Supply.

109
00:08:50.275 --> 00:08:51.859
It's about her shadow.

110
00:08:51.860 --> 00:08:53.153
<i>You find her?</i>

111
00:08:54.946 --> 00:08:55.947
Yeah.

112
00:08:59.659 --> 00:09:00.869
[clears throat]

113
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:04.873
Okay. Not what I was expecting.

114
00:09:06.291 --> 00:09:08.084
Obviously not your place.

115
00:09:09.753 --> 00:09:11.171
What's that supposed to mean?

116
00:09:12.005 --> 00:09:16.925
Just that you drive a 30-year-old Saab.
Not ironically.

117
00:09:16.926 --> 00:09:17.927
And...

118
00:09:19.554 --> 00:09:21.765
this is different.

119
00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:26.728
[Helen] For the record.
I helped pick out the furniture.

120
00:09:31.566 --> 00:09:32.609
For who?

121
00:09:33.860 --> 00:09:35.152
[smacks lips]

122
00:09:35.153 --> 00:09:37.947
Palmer. My ex.

123
00:09:39.199 --> 00:09:44.036
[Daniel] And this Palmer is okay with you
just coming in and out whenever you want?

124
00:09:44.037 --> 00:09:45.872
He's on assignment in South Sudan.

125
00:09:47.165 --> 00:09:48.291
All right.

126
00:09:49.751 --> 00:09:51.127
- Hey.
- Yeah.

127
00:09:52.754 --> 00:09:53.963
Take off your shoes.

128
00:10:07.727 --> 00:10:09.353
Wow. [exhales deeply]

129
00:10:09.354 --> 00:10:13.565
First thing I do when a relationship ends
is bury all evidence deep in the earth.

130
00:10:13.566 --> 00:10:17.570
But this guy's got a giant photo of you
up on his wall.

131
00:10:18.988 --> 00:10:21.240
Yeah. Palmer is not like that.

132
00:10:21.241 --> 00:10:22.491
Like what?

133
00:10:22.492 --> 00:10:23.660
Petty.

134
00:10:24.994 --> 00:10:26.328
So that's what you're into?

135
00:10:26.329 --> 00:10:30.250
- Not-petty. Pulitzer-winning type guys.
- God. it was not a date.

136
00:10:34.129 --> 00:10:35.546
There any food?

137
00:10:35.547 --> 00:10:36.548
Help yourself.

138
00:10:37.340 --> 00:10:39.591
Where'd you go between Steve's and here?

139
00:10:39.592 --> 00:10:41.969
Just walked around.
tried to clear my head. You?

140
00:10:41.970 --> 00:10:43.303
The office.

141
00:10:43.304 --> 00:10:45.347
What office? You were fired.

142
00:10:45.348 --> 00:10:47.475
Kept my key card. Needed a computer.

143
00:10:48.268 --> 00:10:52.438
Okay. So. I did a bunch of searches
on Steve's address.

144
00:10:52.439 --> 00:10:54.940
Oh. turns out. actually his name.
Steven Price.

145
00:10:54.941 --> 00:10:57.651
Finally got what I thought
was going to be his cell.

146
00:10:57.652 --> 00:11:00.237
Recording said the number was not in use.

147
00:11:00.238 --> 00:11:01.321
Maybe it wasn't his.

148
00:11:01.322 --> 00:11:04.450
Well. then I called the number for
the father of Charlotte's squadron leader.

149
00:11:04.451 --> 00:11:05.576
- Mr. Alameda.
- Yep.

150
00:11:05.577 --> 00:11:07.662
Recording said the number was not in use.

151
00:11:09.247 --> 00:11:11.166
It was working the day before yesterday.

152
00:11:13.334 --> 00:11:15.253
Who the fuck are we dealing with?

153
00:11:19.632 --> 00:11:21.009
So do we go to the police?

154
00:11:22.260 --> 00:11:25.597
I'm guessing they're the kind of people
who would make sure that goes nowhere.

155
00:11:27.307 --> 00:11:29.058
These expired two years ago.

156
00:11:31.936 --> 00:11:33.229
No. stop. Ew.

157
00:11:34.105 --> 00:11:35.106
Here.

158
00:11:37.066 --> 00:11:39.402
- You had these the whole time?
- What is our next move?

159
00:11:41.112 --> 00:11:42.363
Do we even have one?

160
00:11:43.281 --> 00:11:45.533
I mean. without that comms recording.
we are move-less.

161
00:11:46.159 --> 00:11:50.246
Well. he said someone in Moldova
recorded the unencrypted comms.

162
00:11:52.332 --> 00:11:54.793
If we could find out who that is.

163
00:11:55.293 --> 00:11:58.671
maybe we can get another copy
of the recording. Leak it.

164
00:12:00.632 --> 00:12:02.842
How do we find someone
we know nothing about?

165
00:12:10.975 --> 00:12:13.894
You know. at Steve's. that chess game.

166
00:12:13.895 --> 00:12:17.606
Weird. right? It's like his whole mood
shifted when his turn was up.

167
00:12:17.607 --> 00:12:19.024
There was something going on.

168
00:12:19.025 --> 00:12:23.404
He was. like. a couple of moves away
from mate. and he just exposed his king.

169
00:12:24.072 --> 00:12:25.823
Maybe he was just distracted.

170
00:12:25.824 --> 00:12:27.534
And what if he wasn't playing to win?

171
00:12:28.993 --> 00:12:30.953
What if he was playing to communicate?

172
00:12:30.954 --> 00:12:31.955
What do you mean?

173
00:12:33.540 --> 00:12:34.958
[chuckles] Okay.

174
00:12:35.834 --> 00:12:38.962
When Snowden leaked
those NSA documents in 2013.

175
00:12:39.462 --> 00:12:42.548
it came out that government agents were
using <i>World of Warcraft</i>

176
00:12:42.549 --> 00:12:44.716
to infiltrate terrorist organizations.

177
00:12:44.717 --> 00:12:49.222
They thought the terrorists might be
using online games to communicate.

178
00:12:50.223 --> 00:12:51.599
What would he be trying to say?

179
00:12:52.517 --> 00:12:57.313
I don't know.
The king... the king has fallen?

180
00:12:58.022 --> 00:12:59.606
Look. it doesn't matter what he meant.

181
00:12:59.607 --> 00:13:01.401
If we can just find out
who his opponent was.

182
00:13:02.026 --> 00:13:03.445
we may have another lead.

183
00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:05.530
How do we do that?

184
00:13:06.739 --> 00:13:11.577
Okay. I caught just the tail end
of his username.

185
00:13:11.578 --> 00:13:13.454
[paper rustling]

186
00:13:13.455 --> 00:13:17.917
It was something. something...

187
00:13:20.754 --> 00:13:22.172
"big foot lives."

188
00:13:26.134 --> 00:13:27.469
Well. that's ridiculous.

189
00:13:28.970 --> 00:13:31.054
- Great. We got him.
- A little. [chuckles]

190
00:13:31.055 --> 00:13:32.307
It's what I saw.

191
00:13:34.934 --> 00:13:36.143
What?

192
00:13:36.144 --> 00:13:38.354
Well. you're good at this. Nancy Drew.

193
00:13:38.897 --> 00:13:40.314
Mmm...

194
00:13:40.315 --> 00:13:42.316
No. no. Don't call me that.

195
00:13:42.317 --> 00:13:45.110
They called you that at school?
It's a sore point?

196
00:13:45.111 --> 00:13:46.863
Call me that again. Find out.

197
00:13:47.947 --> 00:13:50.366
I'll kill you.
I'll kill you in your sleep.

198
00:13:59.334 --> 00:14:01.878
[whistling]

199
00:14:18.770 --> 00:14:23.023
[inhales deeply] Lukas fucking Kyle.

200
00:14:23.024 --> 00:14:24.942
They tell me you've been looking for me.

201
00:14:24.943 --> 00:14:26.611
- [Kennedy] Mm-hmm.
- Mmm. Okay.

202
00:14:27.112 --> 00:14:29.864
I'm afraid you're not gonna like
what I have to say.

203
00:14:31.991 --> 00:14:33.034
What do you have to say?

204
00:14:34.160 --> 00:14:37.288
You and your Outsiders keep
telling people it's safe outside.

205
00:14:38.373 --> 00:14:41.334
- Because it is.
- [Lukas] No. It isn't.

206
00:14:42.419 --> 00:14:44.921
What you see on the screens
in the cafeteria.

207
00:14:45.713 --> 00:14:47.465
that's exactly what it's like.

208
00:14:54.556 --> 00:14:58.268
[smacks lips] Fuck me.

209
00:15:01.438 --> 00:15:03.814
They got to you.
No wonder we couldn't find him.

210
00:15:03.815 --> 00:15:06.316
He was probably their guest
in a big apartment up top.

211
00:15:06.317 --> 00:15:07.526
I've been in the mines.

212
00:15:07.527 --> 00:15:10.904
I've seen the cleaning video. asshole.

213
00:15:10.905 --> 00:15:12.657
I know that they're lying.

214
00:15:13.241 --> 00:15:16.244
It is a fucking paradise out there.

215
00:15:17.078 --> 00:15:19.163
That video gets put in the helmets

216
00:15:19.164 --> 00:15:23.126
so whoever they send outside
actually cleans.

217
00:15:27.172 --> 00:15:28.298
[chuckles]

218
00:15:29.382 --> 00:15:30.717
Video in the helmet?

219
00:15:43.271 --> 00:15:44.563
You believe him?

220
00:15:44.564 --> 00:15:45.565
Why would he lie?

221
00:15:46.149 --> 00:15:47.566
"Why would he lie?"

222
00:15:47.567 --> 00:15:48.902
- Are you fucking...
- Shit.

223
00:15:49.527 --> 00:15:51.653
- [Kennedy] What are you doing?
- [grunts]

224
00:15:51.654 --> 00:15:53.906
Raiders are looking for somebody.
This level's crawling.

225
00:15:53.907 --> 00:15:54.990
[Kennedy] All right.

226
00:15:54.991 --> 00:15:58.160
[Lukas] Look. whether you believe me
or not. it doesn't matter.

227
00:15:58.161 --> 00:16:00.287
These three kept me from being hauled in
by the raiders.

228
00:16:00.288 --> 00:16:02.664
And they wanted me to meet you.
I figured I owed them that.

229
00:16:02.665 --> 00:16:03.749
- but now I gotta go.
- No!

230
00:16:03.750 --> 00:16:05.501
[Kennedy] Great.
Go back to your big pals up top.

231
00:16:05.502 --> 00:16:08.045
Hey. Juliette came looking for me
in the mines.

232
00:16:08.046 --> 00:16:09.296
I'm gonna find her.

233
00:16:09.297 --> 00:16:11.925
- Move.
- Nobody's going anywhere. Stay. Stop it.

234
00:16:12.509 --> 00:16:13.967
- [doorknob rattles]
- Shit.

235
00:16:13.968 --> 00:16:16.136
[raider 1] Judicial Security. Open up.

236
00:16:16.137 --> 00:16:18.598
- [knocks on door]
- [Johnny] Judicial Security. Open up.

237
00:16:19.265 --> 00:16:20.892
[raider 1] Judicial Security. Open up.

238
00:16:22.644 --> 00:16:24.686
[sighs]

239
00:16:24.687 --> 00:16:26.314
Looks like you're stuck with us.

240
00:16:30.443 --> 00:16:32.111
- Step back.
- My friend's in there

241
00:16:32.112 --> 00:16:33.904
fighting for her life. I need to see her.

242
00:16:33.905 --> 00:16:36.448
This area is on lockdown.
Nobody in or out.

243
00:16:36.449 --> 00:16:38.075
If you don't step back...

244
00:16:38.076 --> 00:16:40.036
- What are you gonna do?
- Hey. hey. Shirl.

245
00:16:43.998 --> 00:16:45.166
We tried. Shirl.

246
00:16:47.377 --> 00:16:50.212
What if she doesn't make it?
What if we don't get to see her?

247
00:16:50.213 --> 00:16:53.590
You're definitely not gonna see her if
you're locked up for assaulting a raider.

248
00:16:53.591 --> 00:16:55.134
[Shirley exhales sharply]

249
00:16:55.135 --> 00:16:56.469
Let me talk to him.

250
00:17:03.143 --> 00:17:04.644
I didn't introduce myself.

251
00:17:05.311 --> 00:17:06.312
My name is Knox.

252
00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:08.522
I'm the head of Mechanical.

253
00:17:08.523 --> 00:17:11.942
My friend here. she and the mayor have
known each other since they were kids.

254
00:17:12.485 --> 00:17:16.114
She just wants to say hey. tell her she's
thinking of her. then she'll be right out.

255
00:17:17.365 --> 00:17:18.700
Head of Mechanical. huh?

256
00:17:19.993 --> 00:17:21.452
You led the rebellion.

257
00:17:22.828 --> 00:17:24.580
- Well...
- I was down there in the generator room.

258
00:17:24.581 --> 00:17:26.207
Saw all that gunpowder.

259
00:17:26.750 --> 00:17:29.710
I said. instead of marching you upstairs.
we should put you all in there

260
00:17:29.711 --> 00:17:31.004
with the gunpowder.

261
00:17:32.088 --> 00:17:33.423
then light a match.

262
00:17:34.591 --> 00:17:35.842
What do you think?

263
00:17:39.262 --> 00:17:40.430
Hmm.

264
00:17:41.931 --> 00:17:42.932
I think...

265
00:17:44.392 --> 00:17:45.977
I think you're entitled to your opinion.

266
00:17:49.147 --> 00:17:50.773
This is mine.

267
00:17:50.774 --> 00:17:52.316
[grunting. groaning]

268
00:17:52.317 --> 00:17:54.652
[raiders shouting]

269
00:17:57.447 --> 00:17:58.572
Fuck!

270
00:17:58.573 --> 00:18:01.492
[straining. shouting]

271
00:18:01.493 --> 00:18:02.827
[grunting]

272
00:18:08.958 --> 00:18:10.543
[grunting continues]

273
00:18:22.972 --> 00:18:26.350
[Sims] We have a situation.
Mayor Nichols is somewhere on this level.

274
00:18:26.351 --> 00:18:28.019
She may be with the nurse.

275
00:18:28.686 --> 00:18:31.064
All the cameras in Medical were shut down.

276
00:18:31.898 --> 00:18:35.067
You take this corridor.
You take that corridor.

277
00:18:35.068 --> 00:18:37.529
But remember. I need you to be discreet.

278
00:18:54.587 --> 00:18:56.505
How did we miss this. Rob? How?

279
00:18:56.506 --> 00:18:58.257
We-We handpicked that nurse.

280
00:18:58.258 --> 00:18:59.466
You said she was loyal.

281
00:18:59.467 --> 00:19:02.553
- Always followed orders.
- She did. until now.

282
00:19:02.554 --> 00:19:03.637
Until...

283
00:19:03.638 --> 00:19:05.848
She must've sensed
why you were coming down.

284
00:19:05.849 --> 00:19:07.349
If we don't get this done...

285
00:19:07.350 --> 00:19:09.102
- We will.
- [Camille] How?

286
00:19:09.853 --> 00:19:12.229
[Sims] I know
the nurse's file pretty well.

287
00:19:12.230 --> 00:19:16.150
If they get off this level. I have an idea
where she might take Nichols.

288
00:19:16.151 --> 00:19:18.819
- [Camille] Where?
- She has family down below.

289
00:19:18.820 --> 00:19:20.612
[Camille] Okay. Send raiders.

290
00:19:20.613 --> 00:19:23.658
Camille. we need to handle this quietly.

291
00:19:26.244 --> 00:19:27.495
I'll get ahead of them.

292
00:19:28.496 --> 00:19:30.415
This has to end tonight. Rob.

293
00:19:30.999 --> 00:19:33.793
I'll take care of her myself.

294
00:19:47.515 --> 00:19:49.850
[Sims] Johnny. if you find them.
keep it off the radio.

295
00:19:49.851 --> 00:19:51.268
Send a message straight to my office.

296
00:19:51.269 --> 00:19:54.646
We have people on this level.
Send someone to levels above and below.

297
00:19:54.647 --> 00:19:57.900
And when Emerson comes to.
I want anything useful she can remember.

298
00:19:57.901 --> 00:20:00.694
She's alive and she's gotten away.

299
00:20:00.695 --> 00:20:03.530
- Oh. shit.
- I think Sims and his wife want her dead.

300
00:20:03.531 --> 00:20:05.407
What? Why?

301
00:20:05.408 --> 00:20:06.659
No idea.

302
00:20:10.246 --> 00:20:11.498
I need to follow him.

303
00:20:11.998 --> 00:20:14.500
[Johnny] Hey. you! Stop talking to him.

304
00:20:14.501 --> 00:20:16.502
Step away from the prisoner.
or you're gonna join him.

305
00:20:16.503 --> 00:20:19.172
Just telling him this is what he gets
for being an asshole.

306
00:20:28.389 --> 00:20:30.224
[raider 2] This room is locked.
You have the key?

307
00:20:30.225 --> 00:20:32.434
They're going to see us
as soon as we leave.

308
00:20:32.435 --> 00:20:34.353
- We're not leaving through the door.
- Huh?

309
00:20:34.354 --> 00:20:37.648
I basically grew up in Medical.
and I found out a long time ago.

310
00:20:37.649 --> 00:20:41.611
someone got tired of going all the way to
the stairs to get down to the next level.

311
00:20:45.156 --> 00:20:46.782
Okay. come on. Let's go. Let's go.

312
00:20:46.783 --> 00:20:48.408
Hey. No.

313
00:20:48.409 --> 00:20:50.702
Listen. I'm the reason
you started getting your memory back.

314
00:20:50.703 --> 00:20:53.831
- I took you off the forgetting drugs.
- No. I spit them out.

315
00:20:53.832 --> 00:20:56.291
Okay. even before that.
someone asked me to replace them.

316
00:20:56.292 --> 00:20:58.168
- Who?
- Look. we don't have time for that.

317
00:20:58.169 --> 00:21:00.880
Right now.
your choice is with me or the raiders.

318
00:21:19.983 --> 00:21:21.651
- Hello?
- [dog barks]

319
00:21:30.285 --> 00:21:32.161
Oh. sorry.
I-I thought I was the only one here.

320
00:21:32.162 --> 00:21:34.204
Uh... She's friendly. Don't worry.

321
00:21:34.205 --> 00:21:35.582
Sheriff Billings.

322
00:21:36.791 --> 00:21:38.209
I've never met one of you before.

323
00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:41.170
You know.
we don't get a lot of sheriffs visiting.

324
00:21:41.171 --> 00:21:43.173
- especially in the middle of the night.
- [chuckles]

325
00:21:44.007 --> 00:21:46.091
I'm looking for Carla McLain.

326
00:21:46.092 --> 00:21:47.676
[sighs] McLain?

327
00:21:47.677 --> 00:21:50.012
Oh. she hasn't been up here for months.

328
00:21:50.013 --> 00:21:51.096
I'm expecting her.

329
00:21:51.097 --> 00:21:52.222
Fair enough.

330
00:21:52.223 --> 00:21:53.808
- Nice to meet you. Sheriff.
- Yeah.

331
00:21:56.227 --> 00:21:57.771
- What's your name?
- Uh. Mike.

332
00:21:58.396 --> 00:22:00.148
- Mike what?
- Davidson.

333
00:22:01.232 --> 00:22:04.401
Orla Kent's boyfriend.
Got your name from her sister.

334
00:22:04.402 --> 00:22:06.154
Oh. right. Yeah. of course.

335
00:22:07.155 --> 00:22:08.740
Sheila. Yeah.

336
00:22:10.033 --> 00:22:12.075
Have you found Orla yet?

337
00:22:12.076 --> 00:22:13.453
Hope to soon.

338
00:22:14.913 --> 00:22:17.998
- When was the last time you saw her?
- Here. at work.

339
00:22:17.999 --> 00:22:19.291
Just outside Critical Supply.

340
00:22:19.292 --> 00:22:20.418
How'd she seem?

341
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:22.586
- In what way?
- Her mood.

342
00:22:22.587 --> 00:22:24.546
- What she talked about...
- Oh. yeah. No. no.

343
00:22:24.547 --> 00:22:26.465
She seemed good. Yeah.

344
00:22:26.466 --> 00:22:29.052
She'd just been up at that. um...
uh... council thing.

345
00:22:29.552 --> 00:22:31.053
And she was on her way home.

346
00:22:31.054 --> 00:22:32.387
- You go with her?
- No. no.

347
00:22:32.388 --> 00:22:35.265
I was too focused on giving Dandy here
some exercise.

348
00:22:35.266 --> 00:22:36.809
Yeah. the bay we were in was deep.

349
00:22:36.810 --> 00:22:39.104
It means I can throw the ball
and give her a good run.

350
00:22:40.230 --> 00:22:43.398
Yeah. we said goodbye
and I haven't seen her since.

351
00:22:43.399 --> 00:22:45.110
But you don't seem too worried.

352
00:22:48.154 --> 00:22:51.574
Orla's more independent
than people think. family included.

353
00:22:52.408 --> 00:22:54.701
You know. I'm sure there's. uh...

354
00:22:54.702 --> 00:22:57.330
plenty of things she's gotten into that
even I don't know about.

355
00:23:00.417 --> 00:23:01.418
[chuckles]

356
00:23:02.001 --> 00:23:04.421
- Thank you for your time.
- See you.

357
00:23:09.759 --> 00:23:12.053
[panting. grunts]

358
00:23:14.764 --> 00:23:16.473
They've moved on from Medical.

359
00:23:16.474 --> 00:23:18.393
[panting]

360
00:23:19.978 --> 00:23:21.855
[Amy] Here. take this. Take it.

361
00:23:24.274 --> 00:23:25.357
[banging on door]

362
00:23:25.358 --> 00:23:28.319
[Johnny] By Judicial order.
open the door immediately!

363
00:23:32.907 --> 00:23:35.033
- [knocking on door]
- [raider 1] Open up!

364
00:23:35.034 --> 00:23:36.994
[breathing heavily]

365
00:23:36.995 --> 00:23:39.330
All right. Okay. deep breaths. Okay?

366
00:23:39.998 --> 00:23:42.751
Listen. I'll draw them away from you.

367
00:23:43.626 --> 00:23:45.128
When it's safe. go to the...

368
00:23:45.712 --> 00:23:47.921
When it's safe. go to the pump room on 76.

369
00:23:47.922 --> 00:23:50.466
- What? Okay.
- Okay? Seventy-six. Good.

370
00:23:50.467 --> 00:23:52.302
Wait. wait. wait. Wait. Hey!

371
00:23:53.136 --> 00:23:54.637
[breathing heavily]

372
00:23:57.056 --> 00:23:59.016
[Johnny] That's the nurse. Grab her.

373
00:23:59.017 --> 00:24:00.768
- Hey!
- [exhales deeply] No. no!

374
00:24:00.769 --> 00:24:02.728
[grunting] Let me go!

375
00:24:02.729 --> 00:24:03.812
[Johnny] Where's the mayor?

376
00:24:03.813 --> 00:24:06.398
- [Amy] She's passed out in Medical.
- [Johnny] Show us.

377
00:24:06.399 --> 00:24:08.567
[Amy strains]

378
00:24:08.568 --> 00:24:10.653
[breathing heavily. groans]

379
00:24:24.501 --> 00:24:25.502
[grunts]

380
00:24:28.171 --> 00:24:29.172
[groans]

381
00:24:37.555 --> 00:24:38.556
Daniel?

382
00:24:47.065 --> 00:24:48.399
He ran.

383
00:24:49.526 --> 00:24:50.735
He fucking ran.

384
00:24:51.236 --> 00:24:53.196
- [keys jangling]
- [door unlocks. opens]

385
00:24:57.242 --> 00:24:58.243
Hey.

386
00:24:58.827 --> 00:25:00.620
- Hey.
- What?

387
00:25:01.830 --> 00:25:03.248
I thought you chickened out.

388
00:25:04.165 --> 00:25:05.166
So you missed me?

389
00:25:07.585 --> 00:25:08.795
Where'd you even go?

390
00:25:09.796 --> 00:25:10.879
Oh. my God.

391
00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:14.091
There are black ops assholes after us.

392
00:25:14.092 --> 00:25:15.884
and you think doughnuts?

393
00:25:15.885 --> 00:25:17.637
And bear claws.

394
00:25:19.013 --> 00:25:20.014
You're an idiot.

395
00:25:20.849 --> 00:25:22.474
There's a bodega around the corner.

396
00:25:22.475 --> 00:25:26.019
The owner wouldn't let me use his phone
unless I spent ten bucks. so breakfast.

397
00:25:26.020 --> 00:25:27.729
No. I told you we couldn't call Charlotte.

398
00:25:27.730 --> 00:25:29.106
I didn't call Charlotte.

399
00:25:29.107 --> 00:25:31.859
But get dressed.
we-we have an appointment in an hour.

400
00:25:31.860 --> 00:25:34.154
- What? Where?
- Um...

401
00:25:35.321 --> 00:25:36.405
The Pentagon.

402
00:25:36.406 --> 00:25:38.825
[ominous music playing]

403
00:25:45.749 --> 00:25:47.167
[exhales shakily]

404
00:26:04.100 --> 00:26:06.644
[music intensifies]

405
00:26:12.901 --> 00:26:14.861
- [Sims] You need to listen to me.
- [breathes shakily]

406
00:26:17.071 --> 00:26:19.365
- [panting. grunts]
- Move.

407
00:26:20.074 --> 00:26:21.075
Go.

408
00:26:23.578 --> 00:26:25.330
- [softly] Go. go. go.
- [panting]

409
00:26:26.498 --> 00:26:27.499
[whispering] Hey!

410
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:32.003
- They are trying to kill you.
- [whispering] Okay. [panting]

411
00:26:33.171 --> 00:26:35.339
How the fuck did he know
that I was gonna go there?

412
00:26:35.340 --> 00:26:37.674
We gotta get down to Mechanical.
We got places we can hide you.

413
00:26:37.675 --> 00:26:39.843
I need... I need to find Lukas.

414
00:26:39.844 --> 00:26:41.137
Lukas is dead.

415
00:26:41.805 --> 00:26:42.806
No. I...

416
00:26:44.099 --> 00:26:47.310
No. I talked to him.
I-I-I saw him in the mines. No.

417
00:26:49.521 --> 00:26:51.814
Okay. can you at least take me
where you took him?

418
00:26:51.815 --> 00:26:53.900
- The Digger Void is sealed off.
- [panting]

419
00:26:54.818 --> 00:26:56.861
Okay. can you take me as far as you can?

420
00:26:59.531 --> 00:27:00.740
Fine.

421
00:27:08.540 --> 00:27:10.874
Kenny G in the flesh.

422
00:27:10.875 --> 00:27:13.669
- God. Sam the Ram.
- [chuckling]

423
00:27:13.670 --> 00:27:14.671
[both chuckle]

424
00:27:15.255 --> 00:27:16.338
You look good. man.

425
00:27:16.339 --> 00:27:17.673
That's my assistant Helen.

426
00:27:17.674 --> 00:27:19.174
- Hi. nice to meet you.
- Sam Ramsey.

427
00:27:19.175 --> 00:27:21.260
- Shall we go for a walk? Yeah.
- Yeah. Let's go.

428
00:27:21.261 --> 00:27:22.428
How do you two know each other?

429
00:27:22.429 --> 00:27:24.680
- [Daniel] We served overseas.
- [Sam] Yeah. no big deal.

430
00:27:24.681 --> 00:27:26.974
We were in a band.

431
00:27:26.975 --> 00:27:29.017
- You were in a band?
- The Lost Boys.

432
00:27:29.018 --> 00:27:30.227
Oh. [chuckling]

433
00:27:30.228 --> 00:27:31.645
- Uh-huh.
- No. no. no. no.

434
00:27:31.646 --> 00:27:33.522
- Yeah. we did '80s covers.
- No.

435
00:27:33.523 --> 00:27:34.690
Your old boss here used to

436
00:27:34.691 --> 00:27:36.150
- shred on the sax...
- Wow.

437
00:27:36.151 --> 00:27:38.235
...back before we became
boring civil servants.

438
00:27:38.236 --> 00:27:39.862
At least you get to hang out
at the Pentagon.

439
00:27:39.863 --> 00:27:41.655
I'm stuck at a call center.
begging for votes.

440
00:27:41.656 --> 00:27:43.490
Ah. so that's really why you came here.

441
00:27:43.491 --> 00:27:46.118
He wants me to hack into
the voting machines. get him reelected.

442
00:27:46.119 --> 00:27:48.287
- [both chuckle]
- Nice try. K.G. Nice try.

443
00:27:48.288 --> 00:27:49.289
Um...

444
00:27:50.790 --> 00:27:52.040
I need your help. Sam.

445
00:27:52.041 --> 00:27:54.919
Yeah. You wanted a general meeting
about cybersecurity.

446
00:27:55.503 --> 00:27:56.879
I need you to find someone.

447
00:27:56.880 --> 00:27:58.590
[ominous music playing]

448
00:27:59.299 --> 00:28:02.218
[sighs] What kinda someone?

449
00:28:03.261 --> 00:28:05.220
A player in an online chess game.

450
00:28:05.221 --> 00:28:07.139
We have one player's username.

451
00:28:07.140 --> 00:28:09.433
so we just need to find out
who his opponent was.

452
00:28:09.434 --> 00:28:11.977
Doesn't exactly sound like
official government business.

453
00:28:11.978 --> 00:28:14.146
My sister Charlotte
flew in the Iran operation.

454
00:28:14.147 --> 00:28:16.023
Her sortie went very wrong.

455
00:28:16.024 --> 00:28:18.609
but she's the only one
of her squadron who survived.

456
00:28:18.610 --> 00:28:19.986
- Shit.
- [Daniel] Yeah.

457
00:28:20.570 --> 00:28:21.653
She okay?

458
00:28:21.654 --> 00:28:23.447
That's TBD right now. Her memory's shot.

459
00:28:23.448 --> 00:28:25.950
She had concerns about the mission.

460
00:28:26.826 --> 00:28:29.369
And then we managed to track down
a comms recording.

461
00:28:29.370 --> 00:28:31.790
- That's all encrypted.
- They weren't encrypted.

462
00:28:32.707 --> 00:28:34.416
We heard it. It's just 20 seconds.

463
00:28:34.417 --> 00:28:36.586
- but it was one of her concerns.
- Wait. wait. wait.

464
00:28:38.546 --> 00:28:41.466
What exactly did you hear. Dan?

465
00:28:46.346 --> 00:28:47.846
- What did you hear?
- Airplanes

466
00:28:47.847 --> 00:28:51.935
that were no longer controlled
by their pilots.

467
00:28:52.894 --> 00:28:56.397
Now our contact's gone missing.
along with the recording.

468
00:28:58.108 --> 00:28:59.900
You're not really his assistant. are you?

469
00:28:59.901 --> 00:29:02.320
Something really fucked up
happened on that mission. Sam.

470
00:29:02.821 --> 00:29:05.447
- And we have to find that recording.
- And you figured since we played

471
00:29:05.448 --> 00:29:08.409
"Don't You Want Me" and "Rich Girl". I'd
help you get access to military secrets?

472
00:29:10.537 --> 00:29:11.788
I have a sister too. Dan.

473
00:29:12.747 --> 00:29:15.083
And a wife. and kids.

474
00:29:16.167 --> 00:29:18.252
Oh. and I pledged my allegiance.

475
00:29:18.253 --> 00:29:20.796
And signed so many secrecy documents
you wouldn't believe.

476
00:29:20.797 --> 00:29:22.214
Except. no. you would believe

477
00:29:22.215 --> 00:29:23.924
- because you signed them too.
- Yeah.

478
00:29:23.925 --> 00:29:26.552
I have to take a lie detector test

479
00:29:26.553 --> 00:29:27.928
- every six months.
- Sam. Sam.

480
00:29:27.929 --> 00:29:29.305
- I get it.
- Do you get it?

481
00:29:35.562 --> 00:29:36.563
[sucks teeth]

482
00:29:40.442 --> 00:29:43.987
Listen. if it was my sister.
I'd want to know what happened too.

483
00:29:45.238 --> 00:29:49.325
Of course she's an insurance agent.
so unlikely. [chuckles]

484
00:29:53.204 --> 00:29:56.583
If you ever want to jam
for old time's sake.

485
00:29:57.792 --> 00:29:58.960
- call me.
- Yeah.

486
00:29:59.544 --> 00:30:01.838
Right. I better go.

487
00:30:10.305 --> 00:30:12.307
[sighing] Okay. Uh. now what?

488
00:30:18.897 --> 00:30:19.898
What?

489
00:30:20.982 --> 00:30:23.151
Yeah. uh.
that guy was at Alameda's funeral.

490
00:30:25.945 --> 00:30:27.906
He was at my office the day I was fired.

491
00:30:29.032 --> 00:30:30.033
You sure?

492
00:30:34.287 --> 00:30:36.164
Hello. Daniel. Helen.

493
00:30:36.873 --> 00:30:38.416
Why don't we grab a coffee?

494
00:30:39.626 --> 00:30:40.627
My treat.

495
00:30:45.256 --> 00:30:47.467
You're sure I can't get you anything?

496
00:30:48.593 --> 00:30:49.968
Helen. anything?

497
00:30:49.969 --> 00:30:51.261
- I'm good. thank you.
- Okay.

498
00:30:51.262 --> 00:30:54.057
I think we're-we're all... we're all set.
Appreciate it.

499
00:30:56.017 --> 00:30:58.143
- Then I suppose I'll get to the point.
- What happened

500
00:30:58.144 --> 00:31:00.187
to our contact in Baltimore?

501
00:31:00.188 --> 00:31:03.066
Is he dead. or is he just
off being tortured somewhere?

502
00:31:05.485 --> 00:31:08.821
Steven Price now occupies
a highly coveted position

503
00:31:08.822 --> 00:31:11.950
at the Radford Group.
a cybersecurity think tank.

504
00:31:14.077 --> 00:31:17.996
I imagine you were thinking
of Senior Pilot Alameda's father.

505
00:31:17.997 --> 00:31:20.207
- [chuckles] Uh.
- After his son's funeral.

506
00:31:20.208 --> 00:31:23.877
he received a very generous loan
to bail out his brother's woodworking shop

507
00:31:23.878 --> 00:31:26.088
- in Tehachapi. California.
- In exchange for what?

508
00:31:26.089 --> 00:31:27.298
If I may.

509
00:31:28.007 --> 00:31:32.554
the two of you are endangering
something very important.

510
00:31:34.764 --> 00:31:36.224
[Helen] You didn't tell us your name.

511
00:31:37.559 --> 00:31:38.642
I usually like to know

512
00:31:38.643 --> 00:31:41.395
- who's fucking me over. even if they do...
- I am merely a representative

513
00:31:41.396 --> 00:31:45.400
of people who have the ability
to offer you a second chance.

514
00:31:46.985 --> 00:31:51.489
I imagine the <i>Times</i> was
a dream job at one point. yes?

515
00:31:56.327 --> 00:31:58.912
I've taken the liberty
of contacting the editor.

516
00:31:58.913 --> 00:32:00.831
He's open to meeting with you.

517
00:32:00.832 --> 00:32:03.835
despite your reputation
for journalistic fraud.

518
00:32:04.586 --> 00:32:10.133
It would be a shame for your talent
to go to waste over one mistake.

519
00:32:15.180 --> 00:32:16.181
[chuckles]

520
00:32:16.973 --> 00:32:19.516
Go fuck yourself. You got me fired.

521
00:32:19.517 --> 00:32:22.060
All it takes is one phone call.

522
00:32:22.061 --> 00:32:23.062
Think about it.

523
00:32:24.981 --> 00:32:29.486
Cool. So. uh. what kind of. uh.
cash and prizes are you gonna offer me?

524
00:32:30.904 --> 00:32:33.156
In your case. Congressman.
it's not about you.

525
00:32:35.408 --> 00:32:38.828
How fucking dare he threaten
to withdraw care for Charlotte.

526
00:32:40.789 --> 00:32:42.040
[Helen] Yeah. it sucks.

527
00:32:42.957 --> 00:32:44.667
- What?
- Sorry?

528
00:32:45.376 --> 00:32:48.213
That sounded like there was gonna
be a but there. It sucks. but...

529
00:32:49.547 --> 00:32:52.341
I mean. he wasn't technically threatening
to withdraw care for Charlotte.

530
00:32:52.342 --> 00:32:54.051
He just. you know.

531
00:32:54.052 --> 00:32:57.971
he said that the level of trauma therapy
the clinic provides is expensive

532
00:32:57.972 --> 00:33:00.390
- and outside of insurance. and. uh...
- Sorry. I'm... [stammers]

533
00:33:00.391 --> 00:33:02.768
I'm having a hard time
seeing the difference.

534
00:33:02.769 --> 00:33:05.647
[footsteps approaching]

535
00:33:07.315 --> 00:33:10.275
I can... I'm a United States Congressman.

536
00:33:10.276 --> 00:33:11.485
I can get in front of cameras.

537
00:33:11.486 --> 00:33:12.569
I can tell 'em what we know.

538
00:33:12.570 --> 00:33:13.696
Which is what?

539
00:33:14.739 --> 00:33:17.116
- That Charlotte's mission was fucked up.
- Can you prove that?

540
00:33:17.117 --> 00:33:19.868
I can subpoena records.
I can subpoena the comms recording.

541
00:33:19.869 --> 00:33:21.663
Daniel. nothing will be found.

542
00:33:29.754 --> 00:33:30.755
Oh.

543
00:33:32.090 --> 00:33:33.216
Wow.

544
00:33:36.511 --> 00:33:37.929
You want the <i>Times</i> gig.

545
00:33:38.763 --> 00:33:39.764
Excuse me?

546
00:33:40.432 --> 00:33:42.642
Maybe it's time you open up
about your little. uh.

547
00:33:43.268 --> 00:33:45.019
problem with journalistic fraud?

548
00:33:47.272 --> 00:33:49.565
If you had gone
beyond my LinkedIn profile.

549
00:33:49.566 --> 00:33:50.984
you would already know this.

550
00:33:51.609 --> 00:33:54.779
And of course I want a job at the <i>Times</i>.
you sanctimonious fuck.

551
00:33:55.530 --> 00:33:57.948
But I also want Charlotte
to get the care that she needs. you know.

552
00:33:57.949 --> 00:34:00.034
She's your sister. but she's my source. I...

553
00:34:01.327 --> 00:34:03.871
So what am I supposed to do?
Just supposed to go back to my cubicle?

554
00:34:03.872 --> 00:34:05.832
- I don't know. I don't know.
- Be a good dog?

555
00:34:14.132 --> 00:34:18.635
I just hope whatever you do.
will you please keep your head down?

556
00:34:18.636 --> 00:34:20.471
- There will be eyes on us making sure...
- Jesus.

557
00:34:20.472 --> 00:34:22.182
...that we got the message. Daniel.

558
00:34:26.351 --> 00:34:28.729
[sighs. breathes deeply]

559
00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:29.856
What are you gonna do?

560
00:34:33.358 --> 00:34:36.070
The ex is gone another week.
I'll hole up at his.

561
00:34:39.199 --> 00:34:40.575
I have to think. Daniel.

562
00:34:41.492 --> 00:34:42.494
You?

563
00:34:45.496 --> 00:34:47.414
Take me a week to catch up
on all the work I missed.

564
00:34:47.415 --> 00:34:50.335
so I guess I'll just go and do that.

565
00:35:00.845 --> 00:35:01.846
Congressman.

566
00:35:23.618 --> 00:35:25.912
- [softly] What?
- [softly] Huh?

567
00:35:26.496 --> 00:35:27.872
Oh. um...

568
00:35:29.541 --> 00:35:31.000
I just. um...

569
00:35:32.252 --> 00:35:33.253
[clicks tongue]

570
00:35:35.922 --> 00:35:37.048
...you know. uh...

571
00:35:39.759 --> 00:35:44.263
they had me on all this...
the pills. the medicine

572
00:35:44.264 --> 00:35:46.515
and it fucked with my brain.

573
00:35:46.516 --> 00:35:49.017
but I get this feeling with people.

574
00:35:49.018 --> 00:35:50.520
Like with Knox.

575
00:35:51.521 --> 00:35:54.691
I don't know why. but every time
I fucking see him. I just...

576
00:35:56.359 --> 00:35:58.069
You two didn't always get along.

577
00:35:58.945 --> 00:36:01.238
I think what I'm trying to say is.
with you. I feel like...

578
00:36:01.239 --> 00:36:03.783
If someone would do anything
to you. I. uh...

579
00:36:06.286 --> 00:36:09.538
I don't know. it's. like. I would
kill them or something. you know?

580
00:36:09.539 --> 00:36:10.832
That's just what I meant.

581
00:36:14.252 --> 00:36:15.586
It doesn't matter. Just...

582
00:36:15.587 --> 00:36:18.673
[footsteps approaching]

583
00:36:20.049 --> 00:36:22.051
[tense music playing]

584
00:36:38.777 --> 00:36:40.945
Ossie. Ossie.

585
00:36:43.740 --> 00:36:45.200
[in normal voice] Morning. Shirley.

586
00:36:45.700 --> 00:36:48.035
- What are you doing down there?
- I need two to go down.

587
00:36:48.036 --> 00:36:50.872
- Chair team will be here soon.
- No. Can't wait.

588
00:36:51.372 --> 00:36:53.833
We're not heavy. I trust your arms.

589
00:36:58.838 --> 00:36:59.839
Madam Mayor.

590
00:37:00.673 --> 00:37:01.674
Yeah.

591
00:37:07.430 --> 00:37:09.056
The main thing is.

592
00:37:09.057 --> 00:37:12.893
if anyone comes down in the next
half hour. even if they're raiders.

593
00:37:12.894 --> 00:37:15.897
could you just tell them
there's an equipment problem?

594
00:37:16.481 --> 00:37:17.774
That they have to wait?

595
00:37:21.486 --> 00:37:24.822
Yeah. We've been having issues
with the pulleys jamming.

596
00:37:24.823 --> 00:37:26.824
- Might take a while to get them free.
- Okay. Let's go.

597
00:37:26.825 --> 00:37:27.909
Great.

598
00:37:34.624 --> 00:37:36.209
[knocking rhythmically on door]

599
00:37:40.797 --> 00:37:43.632
[Kennedy] Where the fuck have you been?
You've been gone all night.

600
00:37:43.633 --> 00:37:45.175
I was following Nichols.

601
00:37:45.176 --> 00:37:47.886
She and another woman
just went down the gap.

602
00:37:47.887 --> 00:37:50.722
- Who was the other woman?
- I think it was her friend. Uh. Shirley?

603
00:37:50.723 --> 00:37:52.559
- [sighing] Oh. fuck.
- What?

604
00:37:53.560 --> 00:37:55.853
- What?
- What's with the face?

605
00:37:55.854 --> 00:37:58.313
Nothing. I-I just know...
I know where Juliette's going.

606
00:37:58.314 --> 00:37:59.982
- Mechanical?
- No. it's deeper than that.

607
00:37:59.983 --> 00:38:01.733
- I gotta...
- That doesn't change shit for us.

608
00:38:01.734 --> 00:38:05.029
Actually. it changes
everything for everyone.

609
00:38:05.697 --> 00:38:07.656
- Look. I need to go stop her. Get...
- Yeah. no.

610
00:38:07.657 --> 00:38:09.116
This again? [sighs]

611
00:38:09.117 --> 00:38:12.245
Okay. [sighs]
You really wanna know the truth so bad?

612
00:38:12.746 --> 00:38:15.289
- Let's go ask Juliette.
- [Kennedy] She doesn't know shit.

613
00:38:15.290 --> 00:38:17.876
They got her on the forgetting drugs.
She didn't even know who we were.

614
00:38:18.376 --> 00:38:19.585
Well. maybe she would now.

615
00:38:19.586 --> 00:38:21.963
She knew who I was
when she saw me in the mines.

616
00:38:22.922 --> 00:38:24.758
- [Kennedy] Hmm.
- [Lukas] Hmm.

617
00:38:27.510 --> 00:38:28.511
Okay.

618
00:38:29.012 --> 00:38:30.263
Okay?

619
00:38:30.847 --> 00:38:32.098
How are we getting there?

620
00:38:32.932 --> 00:38:35.476
Well. he's got a way.
but you're not gonna like it.

621
00:38:35.477 --> 00:38:38.271
[shushes] Don't listen to the kid.
You're gonna love it.

622
00:38:44.110 --> 00:38:45.945
Hey. hey. Get this shit out of here.

623
00:38:51.117 --> 00:38:53.244
What are you doing in my office?

624
00:38:56.623 --> 00:38:58.749
Sorry. I. um. didn't see your badge.

625
00:38:58.750 --> 00:38:59.751
This your office?

626
00:39:00.585 --> 00:39:02.211
- Since...
- Since the current shadow

627
00:39:02.212 --> 00:39:03.838
hasn't shown for two days.

628
00:39:04.422 --> 00:39:05.882
McLain's nowhere to be found.

629
00:39:07.050 --> 00:39:08.468
Someone's gotta run this place.

630
00:39:09.385 --> 00:39:10.929
And you're that person?

631
00:39:12.722 --> 00:39:14.556
I'm McLain's former shadow.

632
00:39:14.557 --> 00:39:17.393
which makes me
more qualified than anyone else.

633
00:39:17.977 --> 00:39:21.815
And unlike the current shadow.
I've never missed a day of work.

634
00:39:22.774 --> 00:39:24.567
You're not too fond of Orla Kent?

635
00:39:25.068 --> 00:39:26.360
No. She took my job.

636
00:39:26.361 --> 00:39:28.070
Your name is Glenda?

637
00:39:28.071 --> 00:39:29.154
It is.

638
00:39:29.155 --> 00:39:30.532
So she took your boyfriend too?

639
00:39:32.242 --> 00:39:33.576
[scoffs]

640
00:39:34.744 --> 00:39:39.456
Listen. Mike Davidson is no more Orla's
boyfriend than you are mine. Sheriff.

641
00:39:39.457 --> 00:39:41.667
but he does like
to think everyone loves him.

642
00:39:41.668 --> 00:39:45.922
And sometimes because he's an asshole.
he'll go out of his way to prove it.

643
00:39:47.507 --> 00:39:51.052
So. she didn't take Mike from you.
but she did take your job?

644
00:39:51.636 --> 00:39:54.472
[sighs] I shouldn't be so small about it.

645
00:39:54.973 --> 00:39:57.517
To be honest. losing the shadow job. I...

646
00:39:59.519 --> 00:40:00.728
I was a little relieved.

647
00:40:04.607 --> 00:40:05.650
Because?

648
00:40:06.234 --> 00:40:07.402
Because

649
00:40:08.570 --> 00:40:10.947
maybe it gave me
a chance to go home for a bit.

650
00:40:12.574 --> 00:40:15.076
That's on 70. The mines.

651
00:40:15.869 --> 00:40:17.327
Ed Harwood is your...

652
00:40:17.328 --> 00:40:18.329
Father.

653
00:40:19.706 --> 00:40:21.541
The legend himself.

654
00:40:24.794 --> 00:40:26.588
Somebody in trouble for something?

655
00:40:29.966 --> 00:40:32.051
When was the last time you saw Orla Kent?

656
00:40:38.933 --> 00:40:40.226
Wait.

657
00:40:42.103 --> 00:40:43.479
I know this place.

658
00:40:43.480 --> 00:40:45.023
You used to come down here a lot.

659
00:40:45.523 --> 00:40:46.900
You had a boyfriend.

660
00:40:55.074 --> 00:40:56.117
George...

661
00:40:58.119 --> 00:40:59.704
- Right?
- Yeah.

662
00:41:01.581 --> 00:41:03.333
You used to come down to the Void.

663
00:41:04.209 --> 00:41:06.294
You never told me about him. but I knew.

664
00:41:11.007 --> 00:41:13.759
I told you. Sorry.

665
00:41:13.760 --> 00:41:15.260
[mysterious music playing]

666
00:41:15.261 --> 00:41:16.429
What are you doing?

667
00:41:18.306 --> 00:41:19.933
- What. Jules?
- [Juliette] Wait.

668
00:41:26.773 --> 00:41:28.691
Hey. hey. Can you hit the lights?

669
00:41:33.613 --> 00:41:34.614
Come and look at this.

670
00:41:36.282 --> 00:41:38.243
- Here.
- What?

671
00:41:39.077 --> 00:41:40.078
[Juliette] Here.

672
00:41:41.121 --> 00:41:42.122
[Shirley] Yeah?

673
00:41:45.667 --> 00:41:48.628
So there's gotta be a latch or...

674
00:41:50.046 --> 00:41:51.338
Some way to open it.

675
00:41:51.339 --> 00:41:52.590
[Juliette] What is this? Wait.

676
00:41:59.472 --> 00:42:00.765
Wait.

677
00:42:01.891 --> 00:42:03.101
Hey. hey.

678
00:42:09.149 --> 00:42:10.816
Walker said she sealed it off.

679
00:42:10.817 --> 00:42:12.025
Clearly not.

680
00:42:12.026 --> 00:42:14.736
- [metallic clunk]
- [Shirley] I'll go see who it is.

681
00:42:14.737 --> 00:42:15.738
Take this.

682
00:42:16.239 --> 00:42:17.365
And shut the door!

683
00:42:19.242 --> 00:42:21.870
[mysterious. eerie music playing]

684
00:42:43.391 --> 00:42:44.517
[sighs]

685
00:42:54.027 --> 00:42:55.028
[clears throat]

686
00:42:58.531 --> 00:42:59.657
[groans softly]

687
00:43:13.046 --> 00:43:14.881
[music continues]

688
00:43:23.932 --> 00:43:25.642
[typing]

689
00:43:40.198 --> 00:43:41.908
[computer chiming]

690
00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:52.751
- [stammers]
- [typing continues]

691
00:43:52.752 --> 00:43:53.837
Hello?

692
00:43:54.921 --> 00:43:56.131
<i>Who is this?</i>

693
00:43:56.798 --> 00:44:00.175
Hi. uh... uh.
this is Congressman Daniel Keene.

694
00:44:00.176 --> 00:44:01.427
[stammering] Uh. who do I have

695
00:44:01.428 --> 00:44:03.680
- the pleasure of speaking with?
- <i>K.G. K.G.. it's me.</i>

696
00:44:04.973 --> 00:44:07.100
[suspenseful music playing]

697
00:44:09.310 --> 00:44:10.311
Sam?

698
00:44:11.896 --> 00:44:13.939
- How did you...
- <i>I routed this through a burner.</i>

699
00:44:13.940 --> 00:44:15.065
<i>so no one can track it.</i>

700
00:44:15.066 --> 00:44:17.818
But I gotta be quick. so just listen.

701
00:44:17.819 --> 00:44:21.197
<i>What you said about
your sister's mission didn't sit right.</i>

702
00:44:21.823 --> 00:44:23.575
<i>All week I've had an itch about it.</i>

703
00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:25.660
<i>so I started scratching.</i>

704
00:44:26.745 --> 00:44:28.872
And that led me down
a full-blown rabbit hole.

705
00:44:29.372 --> 00:44:31.582
<i>I found something
you're not gonna believe.</i>

706
00:44:31.583 --> 00:44:34.210
[music intensifies. continues]

707
00:44:51.644 --> 00:44:52.853
[knocks on door]

708
00:44:52.854 --> 00:44:54.189
[Daniel] Helen. you there?

709
00:44:58.610 --> 00:45:00.152
Daniel. what are you doing here?

710
00:45:00.153 --> 00:45:02.529
- Sam called. Uh. he did some digging.
- I thought he...

711
00:45:02.530 --> 00:45:05.366
- I thought he didn't wanna help out.
- He found something.

712
00:45:07.911 --> 00:45:10.663
Look. I know you said
you-you wanted to stop. but. uh...

713
00:45:13.333 --> 00:45:18.338
Yeah. I... I. uh. don't know how
to do this on my own.

714
00:45:22.717 --> 00:45:24.843
- This is us.
- Since when do you drive a minivan?

715
00:45:24.844 --> 00:45:27.555
It's a rental.
From a guy who advertises on lamp posts.

716
00:45:28.139 --> 00:45:30.307
It's the closest thing I could get
to inconspicuous.

717
00:45:30.308 --> 00:45:32.017
- He took cash.
- Oh. thank you.

718
00:45:32.018 --> 00:45:33.478
It could be stolen for all I know.

719
00:45:40.026 --> 00:45:41.902
[Juliette breathing heavily]

720
00:45:41.903 --> 00:45:43.113
[music ends]

721
00:45:58.711 --> 00:46:00.964
[mysterious. eerie music playing]

722
00:46:22.318 --> 00:46:23.820
[person coughs]

723
00:46:26.489 --> 00:46:27.490
Hello?

724
00:46:39.127 --> 00:46:40.920
[hoarsely] Hello. Juliette.

725
00:46:45.633 --> 00:46:47.635
[fast-paced music playing]
